  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Legal and Psychosocial Accompaniment to Victims of Armed Conflict in Bol&#xED;var and La Guajira</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">(1) Promoting access to justice for these victims through a process of orientation, advice, and legal representation under the framework of the Government of Colombia&apos;s Law of Victims and Land Restitution (Law 1448/2011);
(2) Strengthening 4 victims&apos; organzizations in the Department of La Guajira to engage in advocacy around Law 1448/11 and its decrees; and 
(3) Providing 375 victims and the 4 organizations in La Guajia with tools for psychosocial support, protection and self-protection from human rights violations, to help them rebuild their lives.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project seeks to provide access to truth, justice and reparation for 778 victims of armed conflict in El Carmen de Bol&#xED;var (Bol&#xED;var), Urib&#xED;a and Dibulla (La Guajira) by:
(1) Promoting access to justice for these victims through a process of orientation, advice, and legal representation under the framework of the Government of Colombia&apos;s Law of Victims and Land Restitution (Law 1448/2011);
(2) Strengthening 4 victims&apos; organizations in the Department of La Guajira to engage in advocacy around Law 1448/11 and its decrees; and 
(3) Providing 375 victims and the 4 organizations in La Guajira with tools for psychosocial support, protection and self-protection from human rights violations, to help them rebuild their lives.
The project is being implemented by CCJ, with a sub-award to Fundemocracia.</narrative>
  </description>
